{"award_age":57.0,"bio_image":"full\/bfada00e38050b2101cdc0a49ab08a74fcd131e0.jpg","category":"Physiology or Medicine","country":"United States","date_of_birth":"1941-05-31T00:00:00.000Z","date_of_death":null,"gender":"male","image_urls":["http:\/\/upload.wikimedia.org\/wikipedia\/commons\/e\/e7\/Loius_Ignarro.jpg"],"link":"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Louis_J._Ignarro","mini_bio":"<p><b>Louis J. Ignarro<\/b> (born May 31, 1941) is an <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/United_States\" title=\"United States\">American<\/a> <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Pharmacologist\" title=\"Pharmacologist\" class=\"mw-redirect\">pharmacologist<\/a>. For demonstrating the signaling properties of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nitric_oxide\" title=\"Nitric oxide\">nitric oxide<\/a>, he was co-recipient of the 1998 <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Prize_in_Physiology_or_Medicine\" title=\"Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine\">Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine<\/a> with <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Robert_F._Furchgott\" title=\"Robert F. Furchgott\">Robert F. Furchgott<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Ferid_Murad\" title=\"Ferid Murad\">Ferid Murad<\/a>.<\/p><p>Currently, he is professor of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Pharmacology\" title=\"Pharmacology\">pharmacology<\/a> at the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/UCLA_School_of_Medicine\" title=\"UCLA School of Medicine\" class=\"mw-redirect\">UCLA School of Medicine<\/a>'s department of molecular and medical pharmacology in Los Angeles, which he joined in 1985. Before relocating to California, he was a professor of pharmacology at <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Tulane_University\" title=\"Tulane University\">Tulane University<\/a> School of Medicine, New Orleans, for 12 years. Ignarro has also previously worked as a staff scientist, research department, for the pharmaceutical division of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Novartis\" title=\"Novartis\">CIBA-GEIGY<\/a> Corporation in New York.<\/p><p>Ignarro has published numerous research articles. He received the Basic Research Prize of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/American_Heart_Association\" title=\"American Heart Association\">American Heart Association<\/a> in 1998. This was in recognition of his outstanding contributions to the advancement of cardiovascular science. That same year, he was inducted into the National Academy of Sciences and the following year, into the American Academy of Arts and Sciences. Because nitric oxide is indirectly involved in the action of this drug, he is sometimes referred to as the \"Father of Viagra\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Louis_J._Ignarro#cite_note-1\"><span>[<\/span>1<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p><p>He is the founder of the Nitric Oxide Society, and founder and editor-in-chief of <i>Nitric Oxide Biology and Chemistry.<\/i><sup id=\"cite_ref-ucla_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Louis_J._Ignarro#cite_note-ucla-2\"><span>[<\/span>2<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> Ignarro holds a B.S. in pharmacy, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Columbia_University\" title=\"Columbia University\">Columbia University<\/a>, 1962, and a Ph.D. in pharmacology, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/University_of_Minnesota\" title=\"University of Minnesota\">University of Minnesota<\/a>, School of Medicine, 1966. He also received a postdoctoral fellowship in chemical pharmacology from <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/National_Institutes_of_Health\" title=\"National Institutes of Health\">National Institutes of Health<\/a> in 1968. He is a member of the scientific committee of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nicox\" title=\"Nicox\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Nicox<\/a>, a French pharmaceutical company, a member of the Board of Directors of Antibe Therapeutics,<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Louis_J._Ignarro#cite_note-3\"><span>[<\/span>3<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> a Canadian drug discovery company, a member of the Board of Directors of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Operation_USA\" title=\"Operation USA\">Operation USA<\/a>, a non-profit organization, and a member of the Nutritional Advisory Board for <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Herbalife\" title=\"Herbalife\">Herbalife<\/a>, a for-profit nutrition and weight-management company.<\/p>","name":"Louis J. Ignarro","place_of_birth":"Brooklyn, NY","place_of_death":null,"text":"Louis J. Ignarro , Physiology or Medicine, 1998","year":1998.0}